task.summary: Default task
attempts to reduce memory usage
reverted clustering to single process until i get it working right. too much memory used, too much CPU, and sometimes horrible load times.
introduced a "SemRequest" class and a req anon object. made loading loans from KL the default. req.kivaAjax will be either the proxy in the browser or kiva's location if on the server.
restructured req,
added "partner" for currency loss liability
redid fav-icon. loaded loans should always be distinct for some corner cases.
added old pics
do a proper redirect on bad requests. :O
wait for 2s to do initial loading of verse data, removed all references to intercomm
removed ejs view engine, made index a static page.
wait time to 1s... shouldn't be number based.
missing app_id from some api calls (the ones using req.api.get())
split the descriptions into separate downloads to allow for faster loading.
trying to make processing faster by removing distinct on loan load when we can trust it.
don't start the background resync until 500ms passes (let UI catch up), wait 500ms after all loans are loaded before processing all loan descriptions.
don't start the background resync until 1000ms passes (let UI catch up), wait 200ms after all loans are loaded before processing all loan descriptions.
only send down the descr array, not the descriptions. pull descriptions when clicked on. added option to block the downloading of descriptions,
option text
moved gdocs call to req. show the dl options
removed getKLUrl, switched SemRequest to used seconds not minutes, added "Final Repayment In" to Loan component

add a "since" method to pull loans processed since a given date... returns full loan object with descriptions (best?) and delays the background resync of loans for 5m rather than 1s. Gets page into a usable state much faster. added "batch" concept to server to provide consistent reads even if it's taking a while.
added loans_processed promise, removed option for LLS until it stores partners, store more batches on server.
req.kl should not cache results.
keep fewer batches, track when user requests old batch.
pre-gzip the responses for loans and partners... descriptions not yet.
highest compression
added GA code to index so that i'll have more knowledge of failing-to-load conditions. added "endDownloadTimer" and calls to report how long various pieces took to complete
loans/since now uses batch # rather than easily painful newestTime (if user puts in very low value)
fix Teams page to style the radios better.
server doesn't need getPartner, added 24 hour cycle for partner pull (untested), if loans/since returns too many, it skips it.
don't cycle kivaloans object every 24 hours. just redownload the partners.
added temporary "restart" to see if i can use this
added temporary "restart" to see if i can use this
moved the groupBy for payments to replace teh existing terms to combine the multiple entries for the same dates (why does kiva do that??) reduces download by ~50KB compressed.
increase concurrent server connections to kiva to 20. changed url format for data requests. /loans/:batch/:page etc.
strip out more and more stuff from the prepped files that i'm not using and put it back on the client when nulls/0/[]
put back the first names as '' until they load instead of "undefined"
removed "addIt", kls_tags are output now, tags are stripped. borrowers array is removed only sends {M:5,F:2}, removed status,
switched to /since/:batch due to url collision,
putting sendStatus back in! oops
correct content type of responses. descriptions are now being pre-compressed to save prep time and a little bit of dl time, some attempts at memory reduction,
bug... funded_amount being blank wasn't being populated but was already being used for still_needed
redid about text, added "what is kiva" for all people finding it through react sites, only show if they don't have a lender id, re-did wording on /live, show how many loans purchased
switch to restart after 12 months.
report memory usage on command line, rename index to server
added memory output and gc to server...
added memory output and gc to server...
added memory output and gc to server...
